x4freetext: PROCEEDINGS OF THE
SPECIALISTS` MEETING ON NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS OF
FISSION PRODUCT NUCLEI, HELD AT BOLOGNA, 12-14
DECEMBER 1979.
-A METHOD FOR THE DETERMINATION OF NEUTRON
CAPTURE CROSS SECTIONS IN KRYPTON ISOTOPES.-
(IN GERMAN, WITH ABSTRACT IN ENGLISH).-
KARLSRUHE 3 MV VAN DE GRAAFF, OPERATED
AT 1 MHZ. THE PRODUCED PROTON PULSES ARE COMPRESSED
WITH A MOBLEY BUNCHING SYSTEM TO 1 NSEC PULSE WIDTH.
2 MEV PROTONS IMPINGING ONTO A LITHIUM
TARGET. THE PRODUCED NEUTRONS HAVE ENERGIES IN THE
RANGE FROM 0-250 KEV. THE TARGET IS METALLIC.
.LIQUID KRYPTON IS USED, CONTAINED IN A SPECIAL
CRYOSTATE. THE USE OF LIQUID KRYPTON ENHANCES THE
ENERGY RESOLUTION BY REDUCING THE FLIGHT PATH UNCER-
TAINTY. THE WHOLE SET UP IS MADE TO PRODUCE AS LITTLE
NEUTRON SCATTERING AND CAPTURE BY THE MOUNTING OF THE
SAMPLE AS POSSIBLE. THE USE OF SOLID KRYPTON WOULD
NOT ASCERTAIN THAT THE MATERIAL IS REALLY IN THE
NEUTRON BEAM. THE TEMPERATURE OF THE SAMPLE SHOULD
THEREFORE BE KEPT BETWEEN 116. AND 120. DEGR. K.
IN THE ACTUAL MEASUREMENT IT WAS KEPT CONSTANT WITHIN
0.05 DEGREES.
.THE SAMPLES CONTAINED LESS THAN 0.1 PERC XE-
CONTAMINATION. 99.99 PERC PURE KR-84 AND NATURAL
KRYPTON WERE USED.
.THE QUANTITIES OF THE SAMPLE MATERIAL IRRADIATED
IN EACH RUN ARE GIVEN IN COLUMN 5 OF TABLE 4 OF
THE MAIN REFERENCE.
.THE AU-SAMPLE (MONITOR) WAS AN AU-DISK OF 7.1483
GRAMS, WITH A DIAMETER OF 2 CM. ALSO A SAMPLE OF
6.953 GRAMS (2.18 CM DIAM, 1 MM THICK) WAS USED.
.THE CARBON SCATTERER WAS A DISK OF 2 CM DIAM AND
3.3 MM THICKNESS, WITH A WEIGHT OF 1.3131 GRAMS.
70 CM FLIGHT PATH, 1.9 NSEC/METER RESOLUTION.
C(6)-D(6) SCINTILLATOR NE230 FROM NUCLEAR
ENTERPRISES. ITS VOLUME WAS 1 LITER. IT WAS VIEWED
BY A PHOTOMULTIPLIER OF TYPE XP2041 FROM THE
COMPANY VALVO. THIS DETECTOR WAS USED AS A MAIER-
LEIBNITZ DETECTOR. THE WEIGHTING FUNCTION WAS
DETERMINED BY MONTE CARLO CALCULATIONS AND CHECKED
EXPERIMENTALLY WITH GAMMA CALIBRATION SOURCES.
A LITHIUM GLASS DETECTOR IS USED TO FOLLOW
THE FLUCTUATIONS OF THE NEUTRON FLUX.
THE VALUES WERE
TAKEN FROM ENDF-B-4 FOR THE ENERGIES GREATER THAN 30
KEV. BELOW 10 KEV, THE EXPERIMENTAL VALUES
OF KOMPE, NP/A,133,513(1969) , NORMALIZED TO ENDF-B-4
BY A FACTOR OF 603/596, WERE USED.
BETWEEN 10 AND 30 KEV THE MEAN OF THE RENORMALIZED
VALUES OF KOMPE AND THE VALUES OF ENDF-B-4 WAS USED.
.NO DATA ARE GIVEN AT 25 KEV AND 60 KEV DUE TO
MALFUNCTIONING OF THE PROTON DIRECT COUNT SUPPRESSION
AT THE VAN DE GRAAFF.
.FOR NATURAL KRYPTON THE RESULTS OF TWO INDEPENDANT
RUNS WERE 30 PERC. DISCREPANT. (SEE ERROR-ANALYSIS).
SINCE NO PHYSICAL REASON WAS FOUND THE RESULTS OF
THESE TWO RUNS WERE STATISTICALLY SUMMED.
.WITH THE MEASURED CROSS SECTIONS, THE SOLAR
ABUNDANCES OF SOME KRYPTON ISOTOPES COULD BE
DETERMINED.
.DATA FROM KFK-2918.
G.C.
.BACKGROUND .FROM SAMPLE HOLDER
.FROM SURROUNDINGS.
.ELASTIC SCATTERING (BY MEASUREMENT WITH A CARBON
SCATTERER).
.MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND NEUTRON ATTENUATION IN THE
SAMPLE. THIS IS DONE USING A MONTE CARLO PROGRAM BY
FROEHNER.
